                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">A WoM that works on content we fight would be nice.
<br />

<br />
But, the most important thing is to keep the charm contract.  Which is "pet DPS on mob = ex-pet DPS on enchanter".  When charm DPS diverges, enchanters can build groups and tactics around not being hit.  But if you want a weak charm, you can't expect enchanters to build groups around charm pet control.  I don't think groups built around charm, or the DPS required to justify it, is a good game feature.
<br />

<br />
This doesn't mean charm should be relegated to "groups built around charm" with pets that do mediocre DPS.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
