                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">You forgot to add the option 'Put it back like it was'.... Others may agree charm was broken but I do not.
<br />

<br />
I want to be able to solo at a reasonable rate.
<br />

<br />
In a group I want to be either the safety blanket that allows people to pull more mobs, more quickly and/or the power that lets a group take on impossible odds.
<br />

<br />
In a raid I want something to do other than buff, tash, play a level 50 wizard.
<br />

<br />
Gimping the charmed pet like this is not acceptable to me.
<br />

<br />
Putting a recourse on the pet afterwards is dumbing down the use of charm. I want to have the risk of a wipe after a charm break.
<br />

<br />
The supposed reason for it is that the RvR for charm is wrong. So SOE reduced the reward substantially. Only a few chanters seem to have paid attention to the fact they also increased the risk in a lot of ways [too long to list here]. Anything done to reduce the risk after a charm break is to admit they got it wrong and that this nerf is just that, a NERF.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
